content:
Monitor Queue Members with Reports

You can see all users, roles, public groups, and territories added to your queues. Create a custom report type before building reports on queue members.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To create and update custom report types:
Create and Customize Reports
Manage Custom Report Types

Before you can build reports on queue members, create a custom report type.

Select Group Member as the Primary Object. Queues are a type of group.
Add a label and description.
Choose which category to store the report in.
Select a Deployment Status.
Click Next, and then save.

To customize which fields are displayed in the custom report type:
Edit Layout
Add fields related via lookup, such as Group ID, User ID, User Full Name, etc.
Click OK, and then click Save.
Save your work.

Build a report on queue members. Queue members can be users, roles, public groups, territories, connections, and partner users.

Hereâ€™s how to configure a sample queue members report:

Create a new report. Select the custom report type created for queue members.
Adjust filters so that Show Me is set to All group member and Created Date is set to All Time.
Select which fields to display under Columns.
Add filters as needed, such as Group: Type equals Queue.
Group rows by queue name or ID.
Add charts for a visual overview of your data.
title: Setting up Queue Member Reports in Service Cloud
